<task id="034" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5">
  <metadata>
    <title>P2-CLOSEOUT-03 Frontend auto-trigger: when chat upload completes AND user intent was "summarize", auto-invoke summary</title>
    <status>🔲</status>
    <status-note>Closeout task added 2026-06-04 per operator UX clarification: user does NOT expect to issue a third message after upload — when intent + file are both present, summary should run automatically. See notes/summarize-vertical-remediation-plan.md §3.3 (pattern B chosen for Phase 2 closeout; pattern A backend-injection deferred to R6).</status-note>
    <estimated-effort>1 hour</estimated-effort>
    <actual-effort></actual-effort>
    <assigned>AI Agent</assigned>
    <started></started>
    <completed></completed>
    <phase>Phase 2 — Vertical Slice + Insights Tool Integration (CLOSEOUT)</phase>
    <wave>P2-G10-CLOSEOUT (serial; runs AFTER 032+033 deployed and verified backend-side)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>032 (upload populates UploadedFiles[]), 033 (chat agent sees uploaded files), 015 (InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool), 019 (slash-command menu — same intent-recognition trigger words)</dependencies>
    <tags>pcf, react, fluent-ui, frontend, chat, closeout, sev-1-fix</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Add a frontend auto-trigger so that when a chat session upload completes
    AND the user's most recent message expressed a Summarize intent (per a
    narrow whitelist), the chat automatically sends a Summarize follow-up
    message without requiring the user to type a third message.

    Operator UX expectation clarified 2026-06-04: the user says "let's
    summarize" → Assistant says "please upload" → user uploads → summary
    RUNS AUTOMATICALLY. The user should NOT have to type "/summarize" or
    "summarize it" as a third message.

    Implementation pattern B per notes/summarize-vertical-remediation-plan.md
    §3.3 (chosen for Phase 2 closeout; backend system-message injection
    pattern A is R6 territory):

    1. In SprkChat.tsx (or SprkChatUploadZone's onUploadComplete handler),
       capture a new lightweight `intent` hint per session: the last user
       message's intent classification. Maintain it as React state in the
       SprkChat component scope.

    2. On each user message sent, run a NARROW trigger-phrase check (CASE
       INSENSITIVE; whitespace-normalized; full-word match):
       - "summarize" / "summary" / "summarise"
       - "tldr" / "tl;dr"
       - "/summarize" (literal slash command typed but not yet recognized
         as a command)
       - "let's summarize" / "summarize this" / "summarize the document"
       - similar narrow variations
       If a trigger matches → set session-scoped intent state to
       `'summarize-pending-file'` along with the timestamp.

    3. On successful upload (the SprkChatUploadZone.onUploadComplete
       callback fires with the 202 response), check session-scoped intent:
       - IF `intent === 'summarize-pending-file'` AND the intent timestamp
         is within the last 5 minutes (stale-intent guard)
       - THEN automatically dispatch a follow-up chat message containing
         "/summarize" (so the same downstream tool-call routing fires)
       - AND clear the intent state (so subsequent uploads don't re-trigger
         until intent is re-expressed)

    4. UX polish: when auto-trigger fires, show a brief inline indicator
       (e.g., a subtle "Summarizing your file..." chip) so the user sees
       the system is acting. The chip auto-dismisses when streaming begins
       in the Workspace pane.

    5. Edge cases (all should result in NO auto-trigger):
       - Upload completes but no recent Summarize intent → no auto-fire
       - User typed a non-summarize message AFTER the summarize intent
         (e.g., changed mind, asked something else) → intent is invalidated
         by the subsequent message; no auto-fire
       - Multiple files uploaded in sequence — first triggers, subsequent
         uploads do NOT (one summarize per intent)
       - Stale intent (> 5 minutes since trigger phrase) → no auto-fire
       - User explicitly clicks an action chip OTHER than upload (e.g.,
         "Browse Matter Documents") → intent stays pending; uploading later
         in flow still triggers if no other message intervened

    Add or extend jest tests covering:
    - Intent capture: each whitelisted trigger phrase sets intent state
    - Intent expiry: 5-minute window enforced (mock Date.now)
    - Intent invalidation: subsequent non-summarize message clears intent
    - Auto-trigger fires when intent + upload-success co-occur
    - Auto-trigger sends "/summarize" payload (verifies the message body
      sent matches what we expect downstream)
    - Auto-trigger does NOT fire when intent is absent / stale / cleared
    - Multiple uploads in same session: only first triggers (no spam)

    OUT OF SCOPE for this task:
    - Backend system-message injection (pattern A) — R6
    - LLM-based intent classification (currently using narrow phrase
      whitelist) — R6
    - Inline preview of TL;DR in chat composer before sending — R6 polish

    Acceptance: with this task deployed AFTER 032+033 are live on Spaarke
    Dev, the SC-18 walkthrough (task 035) reproduction sequence completes
    end-to-end without requiring a third user message:
    1. User says "summarize a document" → Assistant prompts for upload
    2. User uploads via [action:upload] → upload succeeds
    3. Within 2 seconds (no third user message needed) — Workspace pane
       starts streaming the TL;DR-first summary
  </prompt>

