  <constraints>
    <constraint>Narrow trigger-phrase whitelist ONLY — do NOT introduce LLM-based intent classification (R6 scope).</constraint>
    <constraint>5-minute stale-intent guard MUST be enforced to prevent surprising users with a long-delayed auto-fire.</constraint>
    <constraint>Single auto-trigger per intent expression: subsequent uploads after the first must NOT auto-fire until intent is re-expressed.</constraint>
    <constraint>NO new PaneEventBus channel (ADR-030 closed at 4); use existing chat-pane-local state.</constraint>
    <constraint>NO snapshotted token state per ADR-028; the existing `/messages` POST uses authenticatedFetch which handles tokens correctly.</constraint>
    <constraint>Fluent v9 semantic tokens for the inline indicator chip; dark-mode tested per ADR-021.</constraint>
    <constraint>React 19 per ADR-022; use existing React state hooks; no class components.</constraint>
    <constraint>Backward-compat: existing SprkChat consumers that don't upload files MUST continue to work unchanged; intent state is purely additive.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <steps>
    <step>Load notes/summarize-vertical-remediation-plan.md §3.3 + §4 row 034 + §5 acceptance.</step>
    <step>Read SprkChat.tsx (especially the message-sent handler) + SprkChatUploadZone.tsx (onUploadComplete callback path) + existing useActionHandlers hooks.</step>
    <step>Design the intent-tracking state shape (probably a small useState in SprkChat). Decide between a hook (useSummarizeIntent) vs inline state — prefer the hook for testability.</step>
    <step>Implement the trigger-phrase whitelist + intent capture on message send.</step>
    <step>Implement the auto-trigger logic on onUploadComplete.</step>
    <step>Add the inline UI indicator chip (Fluent v9; dark-mode-friendly).</step>
    <step>Add 7 jest tests per acceptance criteria.</step>
    <step>Run `npm test` in @spaarke/ui-components — verify all pass.</step>
    <step>Run `npm run lint` + `npm run build` — verify 0 errors / 0 new warnings.</step>
    <step>Build SpaarkeAi code-page bundle (npm run build:prod in src/solutions/SpaarkeAi).</step>
    <step>Commit with conventional message; reference remediation plan.</step>
    <step>Update TASK-INDEX.md status 🔲 → ✅.</step>
  </steps>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="Auto-trigger on summarize intent + upload (end-to-end)">
      <url>https://&lt;dev-env&gt;.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?pagetype=control&amp;controlName=sprk_SpaarkeAi</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Open SpaarkeAi standalone Code Page</step>
        <step>In chat composer, type "Let's summarize a document" and send</step>
        <step>Wait for Assistant response with [action:upload] link</step>
        <step>Click [action:upload], select a small PDF</step>
        <step>Wait for upload to complete</step>
        <step>Verify: within 2 seconds, "Summarizing your file..." chip appears in chat</step>
        <step>Verify: Workspace pane starts streaming a structured summary (TL;DR first, then Summary)</step>
        <step>Verify: chip disappears once streaming begins</step>
        <step>Verify: NO additional user-typed message was sent (DevTools Network tab shows the auto-sent /summarize message originated from the auto-trigger, not from user input)</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>End-to-end Summarize works without requiring user to send a third message. Spec FR-01/FR-02/FR-08/SC-08 all validated by this single flow.</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="No auto-trigger when intent absent">
      <url>https://&lt;dev-env&gt;.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?pagetype=control&amp;controlName=sprk_SpaarkeAi</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Open SpaarkeAi</step>
        <step>Send a non-summarize message (e.g., "What time is it?")</step>
        <step>Click [action:upload] (if surfaced) OR drag-drop a file into the upload zone</step>
        <step>Wait for upload to complete</step>
        <step>Verify: NO "Summarizing your file..." chip appears</step>
        <step>Verify: Workspace pane does NOT start streaming a summary</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Upload completes silently; no auto-action. User must explicitly request summary.</expected>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Trigger-phrase whitelist captures summarize intent on user message send.</criterion>
    <criterion>5-minute stale-intent guard prevents auto-fire from old intent.</criterion>
    <criterion>Subsequent non-summarize messages invalidate pending intent (no auto-fire).</criterion>
    <criterion>Auto-trigger fires on upload-complete when intent + upload-success co-occur within window.</criterion>
    <criterion>Only first upload after intent triggers; subsequent uploads in same session do NOT (until intent re-expressed).</criterion>
    <criterion>Inline UI indicator ("Summarizing your file...") shown during auto-trigger; dismisses on stream start.</criterion>
    <criterion>All 7 new jest tests pass; existing SprkChat tests unaffected.</criterion>
    <criterion>UI tests (in &lt;ui-tests&gt; above) pass on Spaarke Dev SpaarkeAi shell.</criterion>
    <criterion>npm run lint + npm run build clean.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

